title: For Sale/Trade:  Type 84 SKS with AK Muzzle Brake
location: Brooklyn Park, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent: Here is a Type 84 SKS in excellent condition. If you're a collector, you know what that means. This is the original SKS that came from the factory built to take *modified* AK magazines. It also has a pushbutton hold-open on the bolt. These rifles were imported by Navy Arms. Very few were made (some say only about 500), but they led to the development of the SKS-D and SKS-M models.If you're a collector, you also know that the Type 84 usually comes with a shortened spike bayonet. This one has no provision for a bayonet, and from the look it never has. Instead, it has a threaded, AK-style muzzle brake. I have never seen another Type 84 just like this.These rifles came in paratrooper length with one magazine. The magazine and stock were numbered to match the receiver, and those numbers are all present on this piece. Standard AK magazines can be modifed to work with this rifle. It's not difficult to do, and you can find instructions online. But this is not a rifle you buy for blasting cheap ComBloc ammo. This is a collector.I've seen these go for up to $1,500 on Gunbroker. They don't come up for auction very often, and the last one went for $1,100 using the "buy it now" option. I'm only asking $1,000 cash because I would rather avoid the hassle of Gunbroker.
